            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>Mid Herts Divers are a British Sub Aqua Club branch. BSAC are a diving agency that trains to internationally recognised standards. We are a mutual club and not a commercial organisation — we are all unpaid volunteers.</p>
            
            <p>In parallel with the pool sessions, we conduct theory training and then move onto skills in open water. We normally suggest that you give it <strong>2-3 weeks as a guest</strong> in the pool before committing to join BSAC or Mid Herts Divers and only do so if you are happy with us. <strong>No cost in the meantime.</strong></p>

            <h2>Joining as a New Diver</h2>
            <p>Once you are in a position to commit to continue to learn to dive with us, there are 4 things you will need to do:</p>

            <h3>1. Monthly Direct Debit</h3>
            <p>We operate a monthly Direct Debit system via GoCardless. The trainee rate of <strong>£25 per month</strong> includes £10 to use the club equipment whilst you are an Ocean Diver trainee.</p>
            <p>While you are paying the training rate, the club will endeavour to make available to you all the equipment that you require to train in the pool and open water. However, the club has a limited selection of wet/drysuits and cannot guarantee availability of these. If the club is not able to loan you a wet/drysuit, you may need to provide your own to progress your training in open water.</p>
            <p>Once you have qualified as an Ocean Diver (down to 20m depth limit), we would expect you to start to get your own SCUBA equipment — we will of course advise you on this when the time comes. At that point your membership drops to the <strong>£15/month qualified diver rate</strong>.</p>

