            <h3>2. Join the British Sub Aqua Club</h3>
            <p>To join BSAC:</p>
            <ul class="info-list" style="margin: 12px 0 20px;">
                <li>1️⃣ Go to <a href="https://www.bsac.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--primary); font-weight:600;">BSAC.com</a></li>
                <li>2️⃣ On the home page, press the big red "Join" button</li>
                <li>3️⃣ Select "Join via a club" → "Join now"</li>
                <li>4️⃣ On the "Choose a club" page, enter <strong>"Mid Herts"</strong> and click search</li>
                <li>5️⃣ Click the roundel next to our name and "Next"</li>
                <li>6️⃣ At "Choose your club levy" page, click the <strong>£0</strong> roundel and next</li>
                <li>7️⃣ On the membership plan page, click the appropriate option (usually "Full Diving Member") and "Next"</li>
                <li>8️⃣ Continue filling out the rest of the form</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We will be notified when you have joined BSAC.</p>

            <h3>3. Ocean Diver Training Pack</h3>
            <p>For your theory sessions you will need to sign up to independent eLearning (an online training platform allowing you to take lessons digitally). More information is available on the <a href="https://www.bsac.com/training/learn-to-scuba-dive/ocean-diver-course/#tab-1" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--primary); font-weight:600;">BSAC training page</a>, or speak to the training team for guidance.</p>
            <p>Please note that this purchase comes with a code which you will need to register your qualification when you complete the course.</p>

            <h3>4. Commit to Regular Training</h3>
            <p>We have pool sessions at Hatfield every <strong>Wednesday 9pm-10pm</strong>, plus a local open water venue (11m deep) at Arlesey, just north of Hitchin. We then progress to other inland venues that vary in depth between 20m and 35m.</p>
            <p>We live a way from the coast but regularly have trips (1 day, 2 day, long weekend or week long), as well as trips abroad, normally week long. Check the <a href="/calendar/" style="color:var(--primary); font-weight:600;">calendar</a> for planned trips.</p>
            <p>We hope that you can commit your time to come regularly to the pool training sessions and theory sessions as and when required by you and by mutual agreement with your instructor. The length of your training to achieve Ocean Diver (and higher grades) will depend on your availability and how quickly you pick things up.</p>

            <h2>Joining as a Qualified Diver</h2>
            <p>Already qualified with PADI, SSI, RAID, GUE or another agency and have your own SCUBA kit? Great — joining is simple:</p>
            <ul class="info-list" style="margin: 12px 0 20px;">
                <li>1️⃣ Set up a <strong>£15/month</strong> Direct Debit via the link above</li>
                <li>2️⃣ Join BSAC (same steps as above — select "Mid Herts" as your club)</li>
                <li>3️⃣ Come along to our Wednesday pool nights and dive trips!</li>
            </ul>
            <p>No cross-over training required. If you've been out of the water for a while, we're happy to offer refresher sessions. See our <a href="/existing-divers/" style="color:var(--primary); font-weight:600;">existing divers page</a> for more info.</p>

            <h2>Safeguarding</h2>
            <p>As a club, we take the safety of all our members very seriously and especially the safety of children. We have adopted BSAC's BuddyGuard safeguarding policy.</p>
            <p>The club's Welfare Officer is <strong>Sue Howes</strong>. If you are registering on behalf of your child and have any questions about your child's safety or welfare, please contact Sue via <a href="mailto:howes.sue@btinternet.com" style="color:var(--primary);">howes.sue@btinternet.com</a>.</p>
            <p>Training your child to scuba dive will inevitably involve some physical contact between the instructor and your child. If you are ever concerned please do contact Sue.</p>
            <p>In order to assist us in the proper care of your child we do insist that an appropriate adult (such as a parent or guardian) is present at all training, whether at the pool or when we are away diving.</p>

